added.title: The Ad
added.description: To make ends meet, the Wattersons are forced to rent out their house. However, with nowhere else to stay they decide to secretly remain at the house. When they accidentally surprise their guests, an elderly pair of fainting goats, they faint...unsurprisingly.  The Wattersons fear the worst and attempt to cover up this "accident".

added.title: The Vase
added.description: Sick of Granny Jojo's ugly gifts, Nicole encourages the kids to take matters into their own hands and accidentally break her latest hideous vase. But when Gumball, Darwin and Anais try to destroy it, they discover it is more robust than it seems.

added.title: The Box
added.description: The Wattersons receive an unmarked package in the mail. To distract themselves from the urge to open it they all take turns to imagine what it might contain. To Mom it could mean financial freedom, to Gumball it could mean superpowers; to whoever it's actually for, it means they're not getting their package.

added.title: The Love
added.description: The residents of Elmore search for the meaning of love.

added.title: The Nest
added.description: A breaking news report tells the Wattersons that their neighbor is among the several mysterious disappearances happening across Elmore. Their search for clues leads them to find a strange egg, which they soon discover belongs to their own Evil Turtle. The family realize it's their responsibility to track down their pet before she and her brood do more damage to the town.

added.title: Son of Rap Bear
added.description: When Flame Princess is coaxed into a high stakes battle against the indomitable Son of Rap Bear, Finn must help her search for a new strategy.

added.title: Do No Harm
added.description: Finn makes amends at the Candy Hospital while Jake tries to connect with their unexpected houseguest.

added.title: Trash Cat
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a cat who's afraid to take baths.

added.title: Starter Pack
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to stop Muscle Man from messing with Thomas.

added.title: Wallpaper Man
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

added.title: 150-Piece Kit
added.description: Benson wants to prove that he performed a famous drum solo.

added.title: Hug Wolf
added.description: After an encounter with a Hug Wolf, Finn goes through a Jekyll and Hyde-like transformation becoming a hug-wolf himself!

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: Guy's Night
added.description: Pops wants to beat the milk challenge to prove he's one of the guys.

added.title: Bucky and the Howl
added.description: After Clarence learns Sumo's in the school musical, he joins up and enthusiastically promotes the show. On opening night with a packed house, stage fright takes hold of Sumo and he runs off leaving Clarence to go on alone.

added.title: Merry Moochmas
added.description: It's wintertime in Aberdale and Clarence is convinced his winter wish for snow in Arizona will come true! However, his classmate Belson along with his grumpy cousin Gary Mooch are a little tougher to convince.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

added.title: In the Clouds
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a boy get his head out of the clouds and focused on his history test.

added.title: Ghost Princess
added.description: Finn & Jake try to solve Ghost Princess' unsolved murder.

added.title: Fuzzy Dice
added.description: Everyone wants to give Pops some fuzzy dice for his birthday.

added.title: Grudge Match
added.description: Ben and Kevin 11 are beamed up to a space ship where must learn to battle together in order to bring down a vicious alien fight promoter.

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Company Man
added.description: When Clarence loses the ball during a soccer game, he ends up following it into an office building, where he's mistaken for the boss's kid and given free reign to wander around. Will he climb his way to the top of the corporate ladder or end up on the chopping block?

added.title: Watermelon Gag
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets a watermelon stuck in his mouth, he is unable to ask for help and people interpret it as a comedy routine. As Uncle Grandpa's popularity rises, his friendships and morale suffer.

added.title: Lost in the Supermarket
added.description: During a trip to the supermarket with his mom, Clarence discovers produce adventure and coupon intrigue in aisle five...and every other aisle.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Ate My Homework
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa shows up and mistakenly eats a kid's Egyptian diorama for school, he helps the kid bring an actual pyramid to class, but accidentally unleashes an evil mummy on the world.

added.title: What is Life?
added.description: In his attempt to out-prank Jake, Finn inadvertently creates the Ice King's son.

added.title: Neighborhood Grill
added.description: Clarence is so troubled by the sight of his teacher in a social setting outside of school, he can't stop himself from intruding on her doomed blind date.

added.title: Halt and Catch Silico
added.description: When a series of negative articles about the Powerpuff Girls are posted on the Internet, the girls track them back to Silico.

added.title: Rainy Day
added.description: The girls get into trouble when left to entertain themselves on a rainy day.

added.title: Electric Buttercup
added.description: Buttercup gets more than she bargained for when she makes a deal with a cool '80s metalhead to get a sweet new guitar.

added.title: Collect This
added.description: Ben finally meets the ones responsible for his intergalactic TV show, and the actor who makes Ben 10 more famous than Ben himself!

added.title: Cough It Up
added.description: Psyphon and a gang of bounty hunters are after Argit, who is in possession of a dangerous weapon!

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
added.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

added.title: Universe vs. Tennyson
added.description: Ben gets dragged into intergalactic court by the other Celestialsapiens (Alien Xs) for recreating the universe (back in "So Long and Thanks for All the Smoothies").

added.title: Weapon XI Part 2
added.description: The Rooters have seemingly turned Kevin and the Amalgam kids against Ben. Can Rook and Gwen help him overcome the opposition and escape the Null Void?

removed.title: Fashion Forward
removed.description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.
